  </table>
  <div class="back-top"><a href="#top">Back to top</a></div>

  <h2 id="sec-2">2. Purpose</h2>
  <p>This document defines the User Acceptance Test scenarios for validating Pulse from an end-user and business workflow perspective.</p>
  <p>The scenarios cover:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Project registration and activation</li>
    <li>Project review and execution</li>
    <li>Task updates, scheduling, and closure</li>
    <li>Collaboration through comments, attachments, chats, and notifications</li>
    <li>Template and setup maintenance</li>
    <li>Roadmap governance and synchronization</li>
    <li>Reports and project comparison</li>
    <li>Negative and access-control validation</li>
    <li>Regression validation prior to release</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The purpose of this document is to confirm that Pulse supports expected business workflows, enforces intended access restrictions, and is ready for operational deployment.</p>
  <div class="back-top"><a href="#top">Back to top</a></div>

  <h2 id="sec-3">3. Scope</h2>
  <h3>3.1 In Scope</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Projects</li>
    <li>Status Board</li>
    <li>Tasks</li>
    <li>View</li>
    <li>Chats</li>
    <li>Notifications</li>
    <li>Categories</li>
    <li>Fields</li>
    <li>Forms</li>
    <li>Maturity</li>
    <li>Product Division</li>
    <li>Product Group</li>
    <li>Roadmap</li>
    <li>Reports</li>
    <li>Negative and Access Control Scenarios</li>
    <li>Regression Validation</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>3.2 Out of Scope</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Performance and load testing</li>
    <li>Security penetration testing</li>
    <li>Mobile responsiveness validation</li>
    <li>Unsupported browser testing</li>
    <li>Back-end API validation not visible through business workflows</li>
    <li>Data migration validation unless specifically requested</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="back-top"><a href="#top">Back to top</a></div>

  <h2 id="sec-4">4. Objectives</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Confirm that business users can complete core Pulse workflows successfully.</li>
    <li>Validate that project owners can register, manage, configure, and monitor projects.</li>
    <li>Confirm that task owners can update assigned work, provide evidence, and close tasks.</li>
    <li>Validate that template managers can maintain reusable configuration records.</li>
    <li>Confirm that collaboration features such as comments, chats, attachments, and notifications work correctly.</li>
    <li>Validate that reporting functions support monitoring, export, and comparison needs.</li>
    <li>Confirm that access control prevents unauthorized actions.</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="back-top"><a href="#top">Back to top</a></div>

  <h2 id="sec-5">5. Entry Criteria</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>UAT environment is available</li>
    <li>Required users and roles are provisioned</li>
    <li>Required test data exists</li>
    <li>Functional QA testing is completed</li>
    <li>Known issue list is shared</li>
    <li>Release scope is confirmed</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="back-top"><a href="#top">Back to top</a></div>

  <h2 id="sec-6">6. Exit Criteria</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>All in-scope scenarios have been executed</li>
    <li>Critical and high defects are resolved or formally accepted</li>
    <li>Regression checklist is completed</li>
    <li>Business approval is recorded</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="back-top"><a href="#top">Back to top</a></div>

  <h2 id="sec-7">7. Test Roles</h2>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Role</th><th>Primary Focus</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Daily User / Task Owner</td><td>Tasks, notifications, comments, attachments, task closure</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Project Owner</td><td>Register, Projects, Project Review, Project Configuration, Status Board</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Project Member</td><td>Assigned work, collaboration, task updates, review visibility</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Template Manager</td><td>Categories, Fields, Forms, Maturity, Product Division, Product Group, Roadmap</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Administrator</td><td>Access governance, controlled actions, maintenance</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Report Viewer</td><td>Project Export, Monitoring Matrix, Project Comparison</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="back-top"><a href="#top">Back to top</a></div>

  <h2 id="sec-8">8. Required Test Data</h2>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Data Type</th><th>Minimum Requirement</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Plants / Sites</td><td>At least one active site</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Users</td><td>At least two project users and one admin/template manager</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Product Division</td><td>At least one active value</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Product Group</td><td>At least one active value</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Product Codes</td><td>At least two values</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Category</td><td>At least one active value</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Maturity</td><td>At least one active value</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Roadmap</td><td>At least one roadmap with multiple milestones and tasks</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Form / Fields</td><td>At least one editable form with DMS or similar field</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Project</td><td>One active project and one configurable project</td></tr>
    <tr><td>File</td><td>One small test file</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Notifications</td><td>At least one read/unread or active/archived notification</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Chat Access</td><td>At least two users in same chat context</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="back-top"><a href="#top">Back to top</a></div>

  <div class="page-break"></div>

  <h2 id="sec-9">9. Test Execution Guidance</h2>

  <h3>9.1 Result Codes</h3>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Result</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Pass</td><td>Scenario completed and expected result met</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Fail</td><td>Scenario completed but expected result not met</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Blocked</td><td>Scenario could not be executed</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Not Applicable</td><td>Scenario does not apply to test role or scope</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h3>9.2 Evidence Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Screenshot</li>
    <li>Export file</li>
    <li>Project ID</li>
    <li>Task ID</li>
    <li>Notification reference</li>
    <li>Chat timestamp</li>
    <li>Defect ID</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>9.3 Defect Logging</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Record the exact step where the issue occurred</li>
    <li>Capture evidence</li>
    <li>Log a defect</li>
    <li>Reference the defect ID in the test execution result</li>
  </ol>
  <div class="back-top"><a href="#top">Back to top</a></div>

  <div class="page-break"></div>

  <h2 id="sec-10">10. Formal Test Cases</h2>

  <div class="section-banner" id="sec-10-1">10.1 Projects</div>

  <h4 id="UAT-PROJ-001">10.1.1 UAT-PROJ-001 - Register Project - Auto-Start On Specific Milestone</h4>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Field</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Test Case ID</td><td>UAT-PROJ-001</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Module</td><td>Projects</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Test Scenario</td><td>Register Project - Auto-Start On Specific Milestone</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Objective</td><td>Verify that a project can be created and started directly on a selected milestone</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Primary Role</td><td>Project Owner</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Priority</td><td>High</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Preconditions</td><td>User has Register access. A roadmap exists with at least three milestones. Required plant, product, category, maturity, owner, and date values are available</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Test Data</td><td>Roadmap with Milestone 1, Milestone 2, and Milestone 3. Select Milestone 2 as starting milestone</td></tr>
  </table>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Step No.</th><th>Test Step</th><th>Expected Result</th></tr>
    <tr><td>1</td><td>Open Register</td><td>Register screen opens</td></tr>
    <tr><td>2</td><td>Enter required project details</td><td>Required fields accept valid inputs</td></tr>
    <tr><td>3</td><td>Select start immediately option</td><td>Start option is accepted</td></tr>
    <tr><td>4</td><td>Select Milestone 2 as starting milestone</td><td>Selected milestone is retained</td></tr>
    <tr><td>5</td><td>Save the project</td><td>Project is created successfully</td></tr>
    <tr><td>6</td><td>Open created project from Projects, Project Review, or Status Board</td><td>Project is visible</td></tr>
    <tr><td>7</td><td>Verify status and milestone status</td><td>Selected milestone is active, current, or positioned as the start according to Pulse rules</td></tr>
  </table>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Execution Field</th><th>Value</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Tester</td><td></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Execution Date</td><td></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Result</td><td></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Defect ID</td><td></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Evidence Reference</td><td></td></tr>
    <tr><td>Comments</td><td></td></tr>
  </table>

  <h4 id="UAT-PROJ-002">10.1.2 UAT-PROJ-002 - Register Project - Create Only To Be Started In Status Board</h4>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Field</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Test Case ID</td><td>UAT-PROJ-002</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Module</td><td>Projects</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Test Scenario</td><td>Register Project - Create Only To Be Started In Status Board</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Objective</td><td>Verify that a project can be created without immediately starting execution</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Primary Role</td><td>Project Owner</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Priority</td><td>High</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Preconditions</td><td>User has Register access and project creation permission</td></tr>
  </table>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Step No.</th><th>Test Step</th><th>Expected Result</th></tr>
    <tr><td>1</td><td>Open Register</td><td>Register screen opens</td></tr>
    <tr><td>2</td><td>Enter all required project details</td><td>Data is accepted</td></tr>
    <tr><td>3</td><td>Select create-only, draft, inactive, or non-start option</td><td>Create-only state is selected</td></tr>
    <tr><td>4</td><td>Save the project</td><td>Project record is created</td></tr>
    <tr><td>5</td><td>Open Status Board</td><td>Status Board opens</td></tr>
    <tr><td>6</td><td>Locate the created project</td><td>Created project is visible</td></tr>
    <tr><td>7</td><td>Start or activate project if included in scope</td><td>Project can be started from Status Board</td></tr>
  </table>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Execution Field</th><th>Value</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Tester</td><td></td></tr>
