  <h2 id="sec-14">14. Appendices</h2>

  <h3>14.1 Suggested UAT Execution Order</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Validate access and test data setup</li>
    <li>Validate template setup records</li>
    <li>Register projects using both start paths</li>
    <li>Validate Project Review, tasks, comments, chats, and progress</li>
    <li>Validate Project Configuration changes</li>
    <li>Validate Status Board changes</li>
    <li>Validate Tasks and View workflows</li>
    <li>Validate Notifications and Chats with multiple users</li>
    <li>Validate Reports</li>
    <li>Execute access control scenarios</li>
    <li>Complete regression checklist</li>
    <li>Review defects and obtain sign-off</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>14.2 Evidence Naming Convention</h3>
  <p>Use:</p>
  <p><code>&lt;ScenarioID&gt;_&lt;TesterInitials&gt;_&lt;YYYYMMDD&gt;_&lt;ShortDescription&gt;</code></p>
  <p>Examples:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>UAT-PROJ-001_CL_20260528_AutoStartMilestone.png</code></li>
    <li><code>UAT-REP-001_CL_20260528_ProjectExport.xlsx</code></li>
    <li><code>UAT-CHAT-002_CL_20260528_TwoUserMessage.png</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>14.3 Severity Guidance</h3>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Severity</th><th>Definition</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Critical</td><td>Core workflow blocked and no workaround exists</td></tr>
    <tr><td>High</td><td>Major workflow issue with significant impact</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Medium</td><td>Functional issue with workaround</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Low</td><td>Cosmetic or minor usability issue</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h3>14.4 Priority Guidance</h3>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Priority</th><th>Definition</th></tr>
    <tr><td>High</td><td>Must be executed and required for release confidence</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Medium</td><td>Important business coverage</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Low</td><td>Supporting validation if time permits</td></tr>
  </table>

  <h3>14.5 Common UAT Notes</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Confirm role, plant scope, and membership before raising an access defect</li>
    <li>Do not treat missing access as a defect until setup is verified</li>
    <li>Use comments for traceable decisions and chat for discussion</li>
    <li>Attach evidence to the most specific record possible</li>
    <li>Do not delete shared setup data unless it is test-only</li>
    <li>Use controlled roadmap or project data for update and retrieval testing</li>
  </ul>

